-- Venezuela Approves Terms on $417 Million Loans, AVN Reports
-- B y   C o r i n a   P o n s
-- 2012-12-06T13:54:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-06/venezuela-approves-terms-on-417-million-loans-avn-reports.html
Venezuelan lawmakers approved the
conditions of $417 million of loans from  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA (BBVA)  and Japan Bank for International Cooperation to
finance transportation projects and a steel plant, the state
news agency AVN said today on its website.  BBVA will lend Venezuela 162 million euros ($211 million)
for a steel plant, while Japan Bank for International
Cooperation will lend 17 million yens ($206 million) to finance
construction of warehouses for Caracas-Cua train line, according
to the state news agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Corina Pons in Caracas at 
 crpons@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 